---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { SITE } from "../../config/site";
import { amortizationSchedule } from "../../lib/calc/loan";

const title = "One Extra Mortgage Payment Per Year (what it does)";
const description =
  "How to think about making one extra mortgage payment per year, common ways to model it, and what can change results. Educational use only.";

const examplePrincipal = 350000;
const exampleApr = 6.5;
const exampleTerm = 360;
const base = amortizationSchedule({ principal: examplePrincipal, aprPercent: exampleApr, termMonths: exampleTerm });
const monthlyExtra = Math.round(base.paymentPI / 12);
const withMonthlyExtra = amortizationSchedule({
  principal: examplePrincipal,
  aprPercent: exampleApr,
  termMonths: exampleTerm,
  extraMonthly: monthlyExtra
});
const withOneTimeExtra = amortizationSchedule({
  principal: examplePrincipal,
  aprPercent: exampleApr,
  termMonths: exampleTerm,
  extraOneTime: base.paymentPI,
  extraOneTimeMonth: 12
});
const money0 = new Intl.NumberFormat("en-US", { style: "currency", currency: "USD", minimumFractionDigits: 0, maximumFractionDigits: 0 });
const pct2 = new Intl.NumberFormat("en-US", { minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2 });
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} canonicalPath="/guides/one-extra-mortgage-payment-per-year">
  <section class="card hero">
    <span class="pill">Guide</span>
    <nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/">Home</a>
      <span aria-hidden="true">/</span>
      <a href="/guides">Guides</a>
      <span aria-hidden="true">/</span>
      <span aria-current="page">One extra payment per year</span>
    </nav>
    <h1>One extra mortgage payment per year</h1>
    <p>
      "One extra payment per year" is a simple rule of thumb for paying down principal faster. It can shorten the payoff
      timeline and reduce total interest, especially when the extra money is applied early.
    </p>
    <div class="btn-row">
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/calculators/extra-payment-calculator">Model one extra payment</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/calculators/mortgage-payment-calculator">Baseline monthly payment</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="grid" style="margin-top:18px">
    <div class="card section prose col-6">
      <h2 style="margin-top:0">Two common ways to do it</h2>
      <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
        <li>Make a single extra principal payment once per year (e.g., tax refund).</li>
        <li>Add 1/12 of a payment each month (smoother cash flow).</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card section prose col-6">
      <h2 style="margin-top:0">Why earlier usually wins</h2>
      <p class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0">
        Interest is based on your outstanding balance. Reducing the balance sooner reduces future interest, so spreading
        the extra through the year can beat a single late-year payment.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">How to model it</h2>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0">
      Start with your baseline in the <a href="/calculators/mortgage-payment-calculator">Mortgage Payment Calculator</a>.
      Then use the <a href="/calculators/extra-payment-calculator">Extra Payment Mortgage Calculator</a> and compare:
    </p>
    <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li>A monthly extra equal to roughly 1/12 of your payment.</li>
      <li>A one-time principal-only extra once per year.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:12px 0 0">
      Real results can differ based on the exact day the lender applies the extra payment and how interest is calculated.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">Worked example: monthly extra vs one-time payment</h2>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0">
      Example: {money0.format(examplePrincipal)} at {pct2.format(exampleApr)}% for {exampleTerm / 12} years. The base payment is about
      {money0.format(base.paymentPI)}. One extra payment per year is roughly {money0.format(monthlyExtra)}/month or a
      {money0.format(base.paymentPI)} one-time principal payment.
    </p>
    <div style="overflow:auto; margin-top:12px">
      <table class="table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Scenario</th>
            <th class="num">Payoff time</th>
            <th class="num">Total interest</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Baseline (no extra)</td>
            <td class="num">{base.months} months</td>
            <td class="num">{money0.format(base.totalInterest)}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Monthly extra {money0.format(monthlyExtra)}</td>
            <td class="num">{withMonthlyExtra.months} months</td>
            <td class="num">{money0.format(withMonthlyExtra.totalInterest)}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>One-time {money0.format(base.paymentPI)} in month 12</td>
            <td class="num">{withOneTimeExtra.months} months</td>
            <td class="num">{money0.format(withOneTimeExtra.totalInterest)}</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:12px 0 0">
      The earlier monthly extra usually saves more interest than a late-year lump sum, even if the totals are similar.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">How much can it save?</h2>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0">
      In the example above, the monthly-extra option saves about{" "}
      {money0.format(Math.max(0, base.totalInterest - withMonthlyExtra.totalInterest))} in interest compared with making no extra
      payments. Your savings depend on rate, term, and when the extra is applied.
    </p>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:12px 0 0">
      If your loan is already near payoff or the rate is very low, the incremental savings can be smaller.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">When it might not be the best move</h2>
    <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li>You have high-interest debt or no emergency savings.</li>
      <li>Your loan has a prepayment penalty or fee-based payment program.</li>
      <li>You plan to refinance or move soon, shortening the time to benefit.</li>
      <li>You need liquidity more than principal reduction.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">Biweekly programs vs DIY extra payments</h2>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0">
      Many biweekly programs effectively add one extra payment per year. You can often replicate the benefit by adding 1/12 of a payment
      monthly without paying a program fee. Always compare costs before enrolling.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">If your income is irregular</h2>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0">
      Consider a smaller monthly extra plus a year-end lump sum. This keeps the habit in place while letting you add more when cash flow
      is higher.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">Double-check payment details</h2>
    <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li>Confirm the extra goes to principal-only, not escrow.</li>
      <li>Ask how quickly the payment posts to reduce interest.</li>
      <li>Keep receipts or statements showing principal application.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">Checklist: make the extra count</h2>
    <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li>Ask the servicer to apply the extra to principal-only.</li>
      <li>Confirm there is no prepayment penalty.</li>
      <li>Track the payment posting date each month.</li>
      <li>Re-evaluate if your rate or term changes.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">FAQ</h2>
    <h3 style="margin:12px 0 0">Is one extra payment per year a rule or requirement?</h3>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:8px 0 0">
      It is just a rule of thumb. Any extra amount, at any frequency, can shorten payoff.
    </p>
    <h3 style="margin:12px 0 0">Does a biweekly program do the same thing?</h3>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:8px 0 0">
      Many biweekly programs effectively add one extra payment per year. Compare fees before enrolling.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">References</h2>
    <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li>
        CFPB:{' '}
        <a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/consumer-tools/mortgages/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">
          Mortgage resources
        </a>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">Next steps</h2>
    <div class="btn-row" style="margin-top:10px">
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/calculators/extra-payment-calculator">Model extra payments</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/guides/extra-mortgage-payment-calculator">How to use the extra payment calculator</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/topics/mortgage-payoff">Mortgage payoff hub</a>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">What to confirm with your lender</h2>
    <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li>The extra is applied to principal-only (not "paid ahead" toward the next due date).</li>
      <li>There is no prepayment penalty.</li>
      <li>Whether recasting is available if you want a lower required payment later.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:12px 0 0">
      Questions? Email <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>.
    </p>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:12px 0 0; font-size:13px">Last updated: 2026-01-28</p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
